76561197995375161,Recommended,531640,30082149,Posted: 21 February,all,Wingflier,"Eternal is essentially a hybrid between Magic the Gathering and Hearthstone. It takes more inspiration from Magic than Hearthstone.What you can expect are fairly quick matches based on deck building, strategy, and obviously card draw.This game has the fundamental flaw of being as luck-based as any card game however, so expect to get regularly screwed over by bad luck. Keep in mind though that sometimes you can get insanely good luck as well.One of the best things about this game are the plethora of modes available to the player, both against the AI and against human players. There's plenty of content here, even for people who don't enjoy PVP.The learning curve for this one is much higher than any other card game I've played. People who aren't veterans of online card games are probably going to get crushed a lot on ladder against real people, but fortunately there are the tons of other options against AI as well. Technically you would never have to play against a real person in order to unlock all the cards, but it would take longer.If you know what you're doing, this game is extremely generous. I've probably done about 8 hours of research total, but this is combined with my hundreds of hours of experience in similar games. However I haven't had to spend a dime and likely never will have to in order to create competitive decks while keeping my own style. There are plenty of sites online to help new players get started.On a final note, check out Dire Wolf Digital's other card game, Elder Scrolls Legends, which is just as amazing in its own way. If you're willing to invest the time (in either game), the payoff is incredible."
